@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home";
}

    <div style="text-align: center;">
        <img src="VerifiedCredentialExpert-icon.png" class="ninja-img" />
        <h1>Azure AD B2C + Verified ID issuance and verifier Sample</h1>

        <p>@ViewData["message"]</p>

        <button type="button" id="idIssue" class="button" onclick="location.href='@Url.Action("Issuer", "Home")'">Issue Credential</button>
        <button type="button" id="idVerify" class="button" onclick="location.href='@Url.Action("Verifier", "Home")'">Verify Credential</button>

        <br/><br/>
        <div class="normal-text">
            <ul>
                <li>To issue a Verified ID credential, you need to do B2C Sign-up/Sign-in to create your account first as the claims in the Verified ID credential is taken from the account. Click Sign in and sign up if you don't have an account.</li>
                <li>To verify a Verified ID credential, you don't need to be signed in, but you have to have a Verified ID credential.</li>
                <li>When you have a Verified ID credential, you can present in to the B2C sign-in policy and use it for authentication.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>